{"type":"message","id":"f593687a","parentId":"35248083","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:41:24.214Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking for Rafael's top 1-2 focus areas for DataFlow today. Let me think about what's most critical on Day 1 of the sprint.\n\nLooking at the context:\n- Validation sprint: March 8 – April 5, 2026 (27 days)\n- Goal: 20 bookkeepers, 15+ testimonial videos, prove willingness to pay\n- Year 1 target: $250K revenue, 250 customers, $45K MRR by month 12\n\nIt's March 8, so we're literally on Day 1 of the sprint.\n\nAs Rafael, the strategic orchestrator, my top focus areas should be about:\n1. Orchestration/alignment - making sure the Council is synchronized\n2. Validation - getting real data from real bookkeepers\n3. Removing blockers\n\nTop 1-2 for TODAY specifically:\n1. Get Raguel recruiting the first 5 bookkeepers (foundation of everything)\n2. Get Uriel's OCR pipeline ready to test with real data\n\nThese are the critical path items. Everything else depends on them.\n\nKeep it short and direct as Rafael would.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\n**1. Raguel recruits first 5 bookkeepers.** Nothing happens without real bodies to test with. That's the blocker for everything else. By EOD tomorrow, we need 5 confirmed bookkeepers willing to spend 2 hours testing DataFlow.\n\n**2. Uriel gets OCR pipeline live.** The moment we have 5 bookkeepers, they need something to test. Simple, fast, real. Not perfect — real.\n\nEverything else waits on these two moving. 🧭"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":398,"cacheRead":29715,"cacheWrite":39,"totalTokens":30162,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.00199,"cacheRead":0.0029715,"cacheWrite":0.000048750000000000006,"total":0.00502025}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772995278673}}
