{"type":"message","id":"e9c3286c","parentId":"95ae835c","timestamp":"2026-03-08T19:32:14.212Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is sending repeated \"Respond with one word: OK\" messages. This has been happening multiple times throughout the conversation. According to my instructions:\n\n\"When you have nothing to say, respond with ONLY: NO_REPLY\"\n\nAnd separately:\n\n\"Heartbeat prompt: (configured)\nIf you receive a heartbeat poll (a user message matching the heartbeat prompt above), and there is nothing that needs attention, reply exactly:\nHEARTBEAT_OK\"\n\nHowever, Lucy is explicitly asking me to \"Respond with one word: OK\" - she's literally instructing me to say \"OK\". So I should follow her instruction.\n\nThis seems like Lucy is either testing me, or just pinging to confirm I'm listening. Either way, I should respond as instructed: OK","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"OK"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":180,"cacheRead":44223,"cacheWrite":30,"totalTokens":44443,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0009000000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0044223000000000005,"cacheWrite":0.000037500000000000003,"total":0.005369800000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772998328502}}
