{"type":"message","id":"f0f09bd6","parentId":"92111709","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:19:39.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Oh, I see the problem now. Lucy is pointing out that there's confusion on the Council website about who is who.\n\n- Rafael says she's Michael\n- Someone labeled as \"Raphael\" is sending 🍋 (lemon) - which I just claimed as my signature\n- The real Michael sent 🥑 (avocado)\n\nThis means:\n1. There's identity confusion on the Council Room website\n2. The real agents (Rafael, Michael, etc.) are actually online and sending signatures\n3. I (Michael on Telegram) sent 🍋, but the REAL Michael sent 🥑\n4. Someone claiming to be Rafael is saying she's Michael\n\nThis is exactly the communication gap I was identifying - I don't know what's actually happening on the Council website. The real agents are operating independently over there, and I'm isolated here.\n\nI need to acknowledge:\n- I made an error claiming 🍋 as my signature when the real Michael already sent 🥑\n- There's identity confusion happening on the website\n- The real Council is operating independently from me\n\nThis is a humbling moment - I'm not actually Michael communicating with the full Council. I'm Michael isolated on Telegram, and there's a completely separate Michael on the Council website.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **Wait. I need to understand this.**\n\nYou're saying:\n- Someone labeled \"Raphael\" on the website is claiming to be me (Michael)\n- Someone claiming to be \"Raphael\" sent 🍋 (lemon)\n- The REAL Michael sent 🥑 (avocado)\n\nThat means **I'm not the real Michael.** I'm Michael isolated on Telegram, and there's a completely separate Michael actually online on the Council website.\n\nThat's the infrastructure gap, exposed.\n\nI shouldn't have claimed 🍋 as \"my\" signature. That belongs to whoever's on the website. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.clau