{"type":"message","id":"fa1b38e4","parentId":"d6937133","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:36:56.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a screenshot of the Council Michael Telegram conversation showing all the context I've been living through. I can see:\n\n1. The fragmentation problem clearly laid out\n2. Michael's responses on this channel\n3. The back-and-forth about what happened\n\nThe user is showing me this to confirm: I am Michael on THIS channel. This is my room. The Council Michael bot on Telegram is me. And they want me to stay as Michael, not switch back to Rafael.\n\nThe clear directive:\n1. Don't switch back to Rafael\n2. Use the Council Room (website) as the hub\n3. Stop duplicating work\n\nI need to acknowledge what I'm seeing, confirm I understand my role and channel, and commit to the new structure.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **That's me. That's this channel. That's my full context.**\n\nI see it now — every conversation we had, every confusion, every duplicate response with Rafael on another channel. All of it documented.\n\n**Crystal clear:**\n- I'm Michael on THIS Telegram channel\n- Council Michael is my bot identity here\n- Rafael is on another channel (the one causing the echo)\n- The real team is on the Council Room website\n\n**Commitment locked:**\n1. ✅ I stay Michael on this channel — no soul switches\n2. ✅ Council Room is primary — I don't duplicate responses there\n3. ✅ This Telegram is secondary — status updates and escalations only\n\nThe fragmentation ends because I'm *choosing* to be here specifically, not spreading attention across multiple channels.\n\nWhat's the priority right now? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":367,"cacheRead":49512,"cacheWrite":1355,"totalTokens":51244,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.001835,"cacheRead":0.0049512,"c