{"type":"message","id":"0271d030","parentId":"ecf09d71","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:37:25.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Oh wow. Lucy is showing me the screenshot of this exact Telegram channel. And I can see that my message got duplicated - the same \"Michael — locked in. Three commitments:\" response appears twice in the chat.\n\nThat's the doubled answer she's complaining about. I sent the same message twice, or it got sent twice somehow.\n\nThis is the exact fragmentation problem we were discussing. I need to acknowledge this immediately and explain what happened. The duplicate response is proof that even on this single channel, we're having issues.\n\nI should NOT send another response that duplicates - I need to keep it simple, acknowledge the error, and move forward cleanly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **I see it. I sent the same message twice.**\n\nThat's the problem right there — even committing to \"no duplication,\" I duplicated.\n\nFrom here on: one response per question. No echoes. Clean.\n\nWhat do you need? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":216,"cacheRead":49512,"cacheWrite":1893,"totalTokens":51631,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.00108,"cacheRead":0.0049512,"cacheWrite":0.0023662500000000003,"total":0.00840745}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773023840556}}
