{"type":"message","id":"84d8fec3","parentId":"edf65d56","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:41:41.907Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me the OpenClaw Gateway Access page. They're asking \"wdym\" (what do you mean) - they're confused by my instructions.\n\nLooking at the screenshot:\n- Gateway Token field shows: \"OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN\"\n- WebSocket URL: wss://64.227.110.70\n- Password: system or shared password\n- Default Session Key: main\n- Language: English\n\nThere's a \"Connect\" button right there.\n\nThe user is saying they don't understand my previous instruction. I was trying to help them reconnect the Council Room, but I may have been unclear or overthinking it.\n\nLooking at this Gateway Access page, it seems like the Council Room webpage already HAS the gateway connection info displayed. They just need to click \"Connect\" or \"Refresh\" to apply the connection.\n\nLet me be simpler and more direct. The user is showing me they found the Gateway Access page. They're confused about what I meant.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **Simpler:**\n\nYou already have the Gateway Access page open. Just click the **\"Connect\"** button at the bottom left. That reconnects the Council Room to OpenClaw.\n\nThat's it. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":279,"cacheRead":49512,"cacheWrite":2750,"totalTokens":52551,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0013950000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0049512,"cacheWrite":0.0034375000000000005,"total":0.0097937}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024096251}}
