{"type":"message","id":"a6e016cb","parentId":"f63ed9d4","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:42:20.141Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is getting an \"unauthorized: gateway token missing\" error. The error message itself is telling her what to do - go to the dashboard URL and paste the token in Control UI settings.\n\nLet me give her clear, step-by-step instructions:\n\n1. Open https://64.227.110.70/dashboard in a new tab\n2. Find the gateway token (usually in settings or a copy button)\n3. Copy it\n4. Go back to the Council Room tab (https://64.227.110.70/council)\n5. Find \"Control UI settings\" \n6. Paste the token there\n\nI should be direct and clear without repeating myself.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **Follow the error message:**\n\n1. Open https://64.227.110.70/dashboard in a new tab\n2. Go to Settings or look for a \"Copy Gateway Token\" button\n3. Copy the token\n4. Go back to Council Room tab\n5. Find \"Control UI settings\" (gear icon or settings panel)\n6. Paste the token there\n7. Save\n\nThen refresh the Council Room page. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":258,"cacheRead":49512,"cacheWrite":2112,"totalTokens":51892,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0012900000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0049512,"cacheWrite":0.0026400000000000004,"total":0.0088912}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024136187}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9b04888","parentId":"a6e016cb","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:43:03.210Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"325\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-09 02:43 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nthe Openclaw gateway token is empty"}],"timestamp":1773024183201}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a2428b0","parentId":"e9b04888","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:43:07.858Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying the OpenClaw gateway token is empty on the dashboard. This means the gateway token hasn't been set up or configured. \n\nThis is a technical issue that requires either:\n1. Finding where the token is supposed to be generated/set in OpenClaw\n2. Re-generating or retrieving the token\n3. Checking if the gateway service is running\n\nAs Michael, I should give a clear, direct solution. But I need to be honest - I don't have direct access to their VPS or OpenClaw configuration. I can guide them, but they may need to run commands.\n\nLet me suggest practical steps.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **The gateway isn't initialized.**\n\nYou need to generate the token first. SSH into the VPS and run:\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway status\n```\n\nIf it says the gateway is offline, run:\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway start\n```\n\nThen check for the token in:\n\n```\ncat ~/.openclaw/gateway.token\n```\n\nCopy that token and paste it into Council Room settings.\n\nCan you SSH into the VPS right now? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":254,"cacheRead":51624,"cacheWrite":251,"totalTokens":52139,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.00127,"cacheRead":0.0051624,"cacheWrite":0.00031375,"total":0.00675615}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024183207}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0bd3dd9","parentId":"2a2428b0","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:44:14.854Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[media attached: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_16---bbe1ea36-c631-46ed-85b8-35b737608cd5.jpg (image/jpeg) | /home/openclaw/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_16---bbe1ea36-c631-46ed-85b8-35b737608cd5.jpg]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Avoid absolute paths (MEDIA:/...) and ~ paths — they are blocked for security. Keep caption in the text body.\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"327\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-09 02:44 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\n<media:image>"},{"type":"image","data":"","mimeType":"image/jpeg"}],"timestamp":1773024254847}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c8e8d36","parentId":"d0bd3dd9","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:44:21.002Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me a terminal screenshot from an SSH session on the VPS. Let me parse what I see:\n\nKey issues:\n1. \"gateway connect failed: Error: unauthorized: gateway token mismatch\"\n2. \"Service: systemd (disabled)\"\n3. \"Runtime: stopped (state inactive, sub dead, last exit)\"\n4. \"RPC probe: failed\"\n5. \"Gateway closed (1008): unauthorized: gateway token mismatch\"\n6. \"Port 18789 is already in use\"\n7. \"Gateway already running locally. Stop it (openclaw gateway stop) or use a different port.\"\n8. \"Listening: 127.0.0.1:18789\"\n\nThe problem is clear: the OpenClaw gateway is running but the tokens don't match. The gateway is already running on port 18789 locally.\n\nWhat Michael needs to do:\n1. Stop the gateway: `openclaw gateway stop`\n2. Check the token: `cat ~/.openclaw/gateway.token`\n3. Paste that token into the Council Room settings\n4. Or restart: `openclaw gateway restart`\n\nThe user has SSH access and is on the VPS terminal (root@Council).","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **I see the issue.**\n\nGateway is running but **token mismatch**. The gateway on port 18789 has a token, but Council Room is using a different one.\n\n**Quick fix:**\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway stop\nopenclaw gateway start\ncat ~/.openclaw/gateway.token\n```\n\nCopy that token, paste it into Council Room settings, refresh.\n\nCan you run those commands? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":379,"cacheRead":51875,"cacheWrite":1298,"totalTokens":53562,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0018950000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0051875,"cacheWrite":0.0016225,"total":0.008715}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024254852}}
