{"type":"message","id":"a0dfcb4a","parentId":"dc1676a3","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:46:06.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The screenshot shows:\n1. Port 18789 is already in use (pid 55038)\n2. Gateway already running locally, listening on 127.0.0.1:18789\n3. Need to stop it with `openclaw gateway stop`\n4. Gateway service check failed - systemctl is not available\n5. cat /root/openclaw/gateway.token shows it doesn't exist or no file\n\nThe issue is clear: the gateway is running but there's no token file being generated. The command to stop and restart is needed, but there are systemctl errors (likely because this is a container or sandboxed environment).\n\nLet me give Michael a direct fix.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **I see it.**\n\nGateway is already running on port 18789, but there's no token file yet.\n\nRun:\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway stop\nopenclaw gateway start\ncat ~/.openclaw/gateway.token\n```\n\nThe `cat` command will show you the token. Copy it, paste into Council Room settings. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":239,"cacheRead":51875,"cacheWrite":1739,"totalTokens":53863,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.001195,"cacheRead":0.0051875,"cacheWrite":0.0021737500000000003,"total":0.008566250000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024361351}}
