{"type":"message","id":"9a007ade","parentId":"96992619","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:46:50.129Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the image, I can see:\n\n1. Gateway service is failing - `systemctl is-enabled openclaw-gateway.service` failed\n2. The token file doesn't exist: `cat: /root/.openclaw/gateway.token: No such file or directory`\n3. Multiple warnings about Telegram configuration\n4. They've already tried `openclaw gateway stop`\n\nThe issue is that the gateway service isn't enabled/running properly. The systemctl command is failing because the service might not be installed as a systemd service, or it's not properly configured.\n\nI should tell them to:\n1. Start the gateway directly without systemctl\n2. Or check if openclaw-gateway is installed as a service\n\nLet me give a practical solution.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **The gateway service isn't running.**\n\nTry this instead:\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway start\n```\n\n(Skip the systemctl check — just start it directly)\n\nThen:\n\n```\ncat ~/.openclaw/gateway.token\n```\n\nIf that still doesn't work, try:\n\n```\nls ~/.openclaw/\n```\n\nAnd tell me what files are there. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":264,"cacheRead":51875,"cacheWrite":2161,"totalTokens":54310,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0013200000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0051875,"cacheWrite":0.00270125,"total":0.009218750000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024405486}}
