{"type":"message","id":"ffc1a858","parentId":"4bbb6b7a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:48:07.075Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the error messages:\n\n1. \"Gateway service check failed: Error: systemctl is-enabled unavailable: Command failed: systemctl --user is-enabled openclaw-gateway.service\"\n2. \"too many arguments for 'gateway'. Expected 0 arguments but got 1.\"\n\nThe second error is key: `openclaw gateway start` is throwing \"too many arguments\" — it's expecting just `openclaw gateway` with no subcommand.\n\nSo the issue is:\n1. The gateway service isn't running as a systemd user service\n2. The `openclaw gateway` command doesn't take a \"start\" argument\n\nThe user needs to either:\n1. Use `openclaw gateway` (without start/stop) to just run it\n2. Or the gateway might already be running, they just need to get the token\n\nLet me give Lucy a clear fix.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **I see the problem.**\n\nError: `too many arguments for 'gateway'`\n\nThe command isn't `openclaw gateway start` — it's just `openclaw gateway`.\n\nTry:\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway\n```\n\nAnd let me know what happens. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":271,"cacheRead":53416,"cacheWrite":1226,"totalTokens":54923,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.001355,"cacheRead":0.0053416,"cacheWrite":0.0015325000000000002,"total":0.008239100000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024481936}}
