{"type":"message","id":"228aa705","parentId":"f10e9021","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:49:51.777Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the screenshot, I can see:\n\n1. Gateway service check failed - systemctl is not available\n2. `openclaw gateway: command not found`\n3. OpenClaw 2026.3.2 is running\n4. Canvas is host mounted at http://0.0.0.0:18789\n5. Gateway is binding to a non-loopback address\n6. Gateway failed to start - another gateway instance already running on ws://0.0.0.0:18789\n7. Port 18789 is already in use\n8. PID 55028 (openclaw-gateway) is already listening on 127.0.0.1:18789\n9. Gateway service status unknown - tip says if supervised, stop it first\n10. Suggestion: `openclaw gateway stop` or use a different port\n\nSo the issue is: Gateway is already running on port 18789, but there's a binding issue (non-loopback address) and possibly port conflict.\n\nThe fix: Either stop the existing gateway process or use a different port. Lucy should try stopping it first.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **The gateway is already running but there's a port conflict.**\n\nThe issue: `Port 18789 is already in use` and `openclaw-gateway (PID 55028)` is holding it.\n\n**Fix:**\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway stop\n```\n\nThen:\n\n```\nopenclaw gateway\n```\n\nThis will restart it cleanly. Once it's running, check:\n\n```\ncat ~/.openclaw/gateway.token\n```\n\nCopy that token into Council Room settings. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":371,"cacheRead":53416,"cacheWrite":1637,"totalTokens":55434,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.001855,"cacheRead":0.0053416,"cacheWrite":0.0020462500000000003,"total":0.00925285}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773024585822}}
