{"type":"message","id":"83b0aed7","parentId":"12228ec2","timestamp":"2026-03-09T05:08:07.312Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is showing me the Council Room website. I can see:\n\n1. **Chat** tab shows the Council conversation - Raguel, Gabriel talking about Michael's \"hallucinations\" and lemon signature\n2. **Mission Control** tab is selected but showing empty sections:\n   - \"Token Usage by Agent\" (empty)\n   - \"Hourly Token Activity (last 24h)\" (empty)\n   - \"Pinned Messages\" (empty)\n\nThe problem: **Mission Control is empty.** The analytics/dashboards aren't populated yet.\n\nLucy is asking me to help fix this. The token tracking, cost tracking, and other Mission Control features we discussed earlier aren't showing data.\n\nThis is a backend integration issue - the Mission Control page needs:\n1. Connection to OpenClaw API for token usage data\n2. Database or cache to store agent metrics\n3. Real-time updates\n\nI should ask specific clarifying questions about what needs to be populated first.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **Mission Control is empty.**\n\nThe sections that need data:\n- **Token Usage by Agent** — blank\n- **Hourly Token Activity** — blank\n- **VPS Health** — no data\n- **Pinned Messages** — no data\n\n**What needs to happen:**\n1. Backend needs to connect to OpenClaw API and pull token usage per agent\n2. Sync that data to Mission Control dashboard\n3. Calculate costs (Claude Sonnet rates: $3/$15 per 1M tokens)\n4. Display hourly breakdown\n\n**Question:** Is the backend connected to OpenClaw's API, or do we need to build that integration first? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":378,"cacheRead":60256,"cacheWrite":1247,"totalTokens":61891,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0018900000000000002,"cacheRead":0.006025600000000001,"cacheWrite":0.001