{"type":"message","id":"907ae994","parentId":"616b3fe1","timestamp":"2026-03-09T05:20:25.344Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"368\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-09 05:20 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nFix the website please"}],"timestamp":1773033625327}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a4a513b","parentId":"907ae994","timestamp":"2026-03-09T05:20:32.459Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking me to fix the website. The file sidebar isn't loading because the backend server isn't running. I need to build a backend that serves the file list and file contents.\n\nLet me create a simple Node.js backend with Express that:\n1. Listens on port 3001\n2. Serves /api/files (list files in the workspace)\n3. Serves /api/file/:path (read file contents)\n4. Handles CORS so the frontend can access it\n\nI'll create this now.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **Building the backend now.**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_Vak42qI4nZ6iCYvcaCqRVn","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-rafael/backend/server.js","content":"const express = require('express');\nconst fs = require('fs').promises;\nconst path = require('path');\nconst cors = require('cors');\n\nconst app = express();\nconst PORT = 3001;\nconst WORKSPACE = path.expand('~/.openclaw/workspace-rafael');\n\napp.use(cors());\napp.use(express.json());\n\n// List all files in workspace\napp.get('/api/files', async (req, res) => {\n  try {\n    const files = await fs.readdir(WORKSPACE);\n    const fileList = await Promise.all(\n      files.map(async (file) => {\n        const filePath = path.join(WORKSPACE, file);\n        const stat = await fs.stat(filePath);\n        return {\n          name: file,\n          path: file,\n          isDirectory: stat.isDirectory(),\n          size: stat.size,\n          modified: stat.mtime\n        };\n      })\n    );\n    res.json(fileList.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name)));\n  } catch (err) {\n    res.status(500).json({ error: err.message });\n  }\n});\n\n// Read file contents\napp.get('/api/file/:path(*)', async (req, res) => {\n  try {\n    const filePath = path.join(WORKSPACE, req.params.path);\n    \n    // Security: prevent directory traversal\n    if (!filePath.startsWith(WORKSPACE)) {\n      return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Access denied' });\n    }\n    \n    const content = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf8');\n    res.json({ content, path: req.params.path });\n  } catch (err) {\n    res.status(500).json({ error: err.message });\n  }\n});\n\n// Health check\napp.get('/health', (req, res) => {\n  res.json({ status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date() });\n});\n\napp.listen(PORT, () => {\n  console.log(`Council Room backend running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);\n});\n"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":735,"cacheRead":62581,"cacheWrite":181,"totalTokens":63507,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0036750000000000003,"cacheRead":0.006258100000000001,"cacheWrite":0.00022625000000000002,"total":0.010169350000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773033625339}}
