{"type":"message","id":"ff952a57","parentId":"a16f7558","timestamp":"2026-03-09T05:22:55.046Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they can't send messages in the Council Room. This could be several issues:\n\n1. Frontend isn't connected to the backend message API\n2. WebSocket connection not established\n3. Message endpoint not implemented in the backend\n4. Gateway token still missing\n\nI should check what error they're seeing and likely need to add a messages API endpoint to the backend. Let me ask for more details first, or check if there's an error in the browser console.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **Messages endpoint isn't built yet.**\n\nThe backend only has `/api/files`. I need to add:\n1. `/api/messages` - POST to send messages\n2. `/api/chat` - GET to fetch message history\n3. WebSocket connection for real-time updates\n\nQuick question: Do you want me to build that now, or should we focus on getting the files working first? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":205,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":66119,"totalTokens":66334,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.001025,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.08264875,"total":0.08368375}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773033769267}}
