{"type":"message","id":"85539c9b","parentId":"b08a19a3","timestamp":"2026-03-09T06:13:29.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying:\n1. Send button is broken\n2. Pressing Enter doesn't work\n3. They want to upload images and docs\n\nI need to:\n1. Check what's happening with the send button in the frontend\n2. Add file upload capability to the backend\n3. Make Enter key work for sending messages\n\nLet me first check what the issue might be. The backend is working (we tested it), but the frontend might not be wired up correctly. I should add:\n1. File upload endpoint\n2. Better error handling\n3. Maybe check if there's a frontend issue\n\nLet me update the backend to support file uploads and improve the message handling.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ **Two issues:**\n\n1. **Send button broken** — frontend not calling the API correctly\n2. **No file upload** — need to add that endpoint\n\nLet me fix both:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_JRyZHwpn7QjzMx7OLzFPGQ","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-rafael/backend/server.js","newText":"const express = require('express');\nconst fs = require('fs').promises;\nconst path = require('path');\nconst os = require('os');\nconst cors = require('cors');\nconst multer = require('multer');\n\nconst app = express();\nconst PORT = 3001;\nconst WORKSPACE = path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace-rafael');\nconst UPLOADS = path.join(WORKSPACE, 'uploads');\n\n// Ensure uploads directory exists\nfs.mkdir(UPLOADS, { recursive: true }).catch(console.error);\n\n// Configure multer for file uploads\nconst upload = multer({ dest: UPLOADS });\n\napp.use(cors());\napp.use(express.json({ limit: '50mb' }));\napp.use(express.urlencoded({ limit: '50mb', extended: true }));\napp.use('/uploads', express.static(UPLOADS));","oldText":"const express = require('express');\nconst fs = require('fs').promises;\nconst path = require('p