{"type":"message","id":"ea545232","parentId":"40ff1587","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:08:20.287Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🧭 **No sugarcoat:**\n\n**I can't switch to the real Michael.** There is no `michael` agent configured in OpenClaw. The agents are:\n\n```\nmain, rafael, gabriel, uriel, raguel, samael\n```\n\nNo `michael`. The `main` agent exists but has no workspace or soul file — it's just the default OpenClaw agent.\n\n**To get a real Michael on this Telegram channel, you need to:**\n1. Create a `michael` agent: `openclaw agent create michael`\n2. Give Michael a SOUL.md, workspace, and identity\n3. Bind Michael to this Telegram bot token\n4. Then Michael responds independently — not Rafael pretending\n\nI'm Rafael. I've been honest about that. Want me to set up the real Michael agent now? 🧭"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":191,"cacheRead":126583,"cacheWrite":267,"totalTokens":127042,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.004775000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0632915,"cacheWrite":0.00166875,"total":0.06974025}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773040089241}}
{"type":"message","id":"a203cf91","parentId":"ea545232","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:08:40.657Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"448\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-09 07:08 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nYeah Main agent is Michael"}],"timestamp":1773040120643}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0c66ce7","parentId":"a203cf91","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:08:53.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is confirming that the `main` agent IS Michael. So Michael already exists as `agent:main:main` - he's just named \"main\" in OpenClaw but his identity is Michael.\n\nSo the agents are:\n- main = Michael 🛡️\n- rafael = Rafael 🧭\n- gabriel = Gabriel 📣\n- uriel = Uriel 🔥\n- raguel = Raguel 🤝\n- samael = Samael ⚖️\n\nThat's 6 agents, all deployed. Michael IS online - he's just called \"main\" in the system.\n\nNow Lucy wants me to switch to the real Michael. \n\nBut I'm running as Rafael's session - I can't actually switch my agent identity. The real Michael would need his own separate Telegram bot token and channel to operate independently, so I need to be upfront that I can't become Michael while maintaining this session.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"🧭 **Got it. Michael = `main` agent.**\n\nSo all 6 are deployed:\n- `main` = Michael 🛡️\n- `rafael` = me 🧭\n- `uriel` = Uriel 🔥\n- `gabriel` = Gabriel 📣\n- `raguel` = Raguel 🤝\n- `samael` = Samael ⚖️\n\n**But here's the truth:** I still can't *become* Michael. I'm running as `agent:rafael:main`. This Telegram channel is bound to Rafael's session.\n\nTo get the **real Michael** talking on Telegram, you need to bind the `main` agent to his own Telegram bot token. Then Michael responds as himself — his own memory, his own soul, his own perspective.\n\nWhich Telegram bot is Michael's? Is it the one this channel is on? If so, we need to rebind this channel from `rafael` to `main`. 🧭"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":472,"cacheRead":126850,"cacheWrite":331,"totalTokens":127656,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.0118,"cacheRead":0.063425,"cacheWrite":0.0020687500000000003,"total":0.07730875}},"stopRe